00:02:21.800 --> 00:02:23.070
I'M BILL MOYERS.

00:02:23.070 --> 00:02:24.770
HARDLY A FAMILY HAS BEEN SPARED

00:02:24.770 --> 00:02:27.030
DIRECT OR INDIRECT EXPERIENCE
WITH ADDICTION

00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:29.070
INCLUDING MY OWN.

00:02:29.070 --> 00:02:31.800
MY WIFE JUDITH AND I THOUGHT
WE KNEW ABOUT ADDICTION

00:02:31.800 --> 00:02:33.670
UNTIL IT CAME CLOSE TO HOME.

00:02:33.670 --> 00:02:37.130
THEN WE DISCOVERED
JUST HOW NAIVE WE HAD BEEN.

00:02:37.130 --> 00:02:39.600
TEN YEARS AGO,
OUR OLDEST SON PLUNGED INTO

00:02:39.600 --> 00:02:42.670
A LONG AND PAINFUL STRUGGLE
WITH DRUGS AND ALCOHOL.

00:02:42.670 --> 00:02:45.800
OUR ENTIRE FAMILY WAS
SWEPT INTO THE ORDEAL.

00:02:45.800 --> 00:02:48.500
IT'S COME TO A HAPPY PLACE
FOR US, FORTUNATELY

00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:50.230
AND OUR SON IS DOING WELL.

00:02:50.230 --> 00:02:52.570
MANY OTHERS ARE NOT SO LUCKY.

00:02:52.570 --> 00:02:54.830
WHAT WE HAVE LEARNED
FROM OUR EXPERIENCE

00:02:54.830 --> 00:02:57.530
AND ARE STILL LEARNING
PROMPTED THIS SERIES.

00:02:57.530 --> 00:02:59.070
IT'S NOT ABOUT THE USE

00:02:59.070 --> 00:03:02.200
OR EVEN THE OCCASIONAL ABUSE
OF A SUBSTANCE.

00:03:02.200 --> 00:03:04.770
WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT THAT OBSESSIVE DESIRE

00:03:04.770 --> 00:03:07.600
WHERE A CHEMICAL
YOU TAKE, DRINK OR SMOKE

00:03:07.600 --> 00:03:11.800
BECOMES THE MASTER OF YOUR MIND
AND THE TYRANT OF YOUR LIFE.

00:03:11.800 --> 00:03:13.570
THAT'S WHAT WE'LL BE REPORTING:

00:03:13.570 --> 00:03:15.970
THE EXPERIENCE OF ADDICTION,
HOW IT HAPPENS

00:03:15.970 --> 00:03:17.700
AND WHAT CAN BE DONE ABOUT IT.

00:03:19.870 --> 00:03:23.130
Woman:
OKAY, DENISE, NOW YOU'RE
GOING TO HEAR THE BEEP

00:03:23.130 --> 00:03:24.730
FOR ABOUT TWO MINUTES.

00:03:24.730 --> 00:03:29.130
Moyers:
SCIENTISTS WILL SHOW US
HOW DRUGS HIJACK THE BRAIN.

00:03:29.130 --> 00:03:31.630
Man:
LITERALLY,
WHAT THIS ALLOWS US TO DO

00:03:31.630 --> 00:03:35.370
IS GET AN IMAGE OF DESIRE
IN THE BRAIN.

00:03:35.370 --> 00:03:36.670
Man:
NICE-LOOKING BRAIN.

00:03:37.900 --> 00:03:40.170
Woman:
I TELL THE GIRLS ALL THE TIME

00:03:40.170 --> 00:03:42.300
THAT IF YOU FORGET
YOUR LAST HIGH

00:03:42.300 --> 00:03:44.130
THEN YOU'RE GOING TO USE AGAIN.

00:03:44.130 --> 00:03:46.230
HI, I'M LASHANNA,
I'M AN ADDICT.

00:03:46.230 --> 00:03:48.270
Moyers:
WE'LL GO TO PLACES

00:03:48.270 --> 00:03:50.830
WHERE PEOPLE ARE WORKING
TO BREAK FREE FROM ADDICTION.

00:03:50.830 --> 00:03:54.000
AND THE NEW FRIENDS I MET--
THE BEST FRIENDS I EVER HAD.

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:55.630
THEY CLEAN.

00:03:55.630 --> 00:03:56.900
(<i> laughter</i> )

00:03:58.570 --> 00:04:00.170
Moyers:
WE'LL TALK TO KIDS

00:04:00.170 --> 00:04:04.300
IN DANGER OF BECOMING
THE NEXT GENERATION OF ADDICTS.

00:04:04.300 --> 00:04:06.170
I MEAN,
THEY JUST KIND OF TOLD ME

00:04:06.170 --> 00:04:08.270
"JOE, YOU'RE AN ADDICT,
LOOK AT YOU."

00:04:08.270 --> 00:04:10.770
I SAID, "WHY? HOW?
BECAUSE WHAT?

00:04:10.770 --> 00:04:14.200
BECAUSE I HANG OUT
WITH MY FRIENDS AND DO DRUGS?"

00:04:14.200 --> 00:04:18.270
Woman:
THIS WHOLE JAIL IS MAINLY FILLED
WITH PEOPLE WITH DRUG PROBLEMS.

00:04:18.270 --> 00:04:20.930
THEY STEAL FOR DRUGS,
THEY HAVE SEX FOR DRUGS.

00:04:20.930 --> 00:04:22.670
IT'S ALL FOR THE DOPE.

00:04:22.670 --> 00:04:27.770
Moyers:
AND WE'LL REPORT ON THE FIGHT TO
CHANGE OUR NATIONAL DRUG POLICY.

00:04:27.770 --> 00:04:29.200
Woman:
THE BOTTOM LINE IS

00:04:29.200 --> 00:04:31.730
THAT WE WOULD RATHER HAVE
THAT BED SPACE USED

00:04:31.730 --> 00:04:33.730
BY A RAPIST,
A ROBBER OR A MURDERER

00:04:33.730 --> 00:04:38.030
THAN SOMEONE WHO HAS
AN ABUSIVE SUBSTANCE PROBLEM.

00:04:40.600 --> 00:04:42.770
LET'S BEGIN
WITH SOME REAL VETERANS--

00:04:42.770 --> 00:04:45.270
PEOPLE WHO SPEAK
FROM PERSONAL EXPERIENCE.

00:04:45.270 --> 00:04:47.600
THEY'VE AGREED
TO TELL US THEIR STORIES

00:04:47.600 --> 00:04:51.170
SO WE COULD BRING YOU
THIS "PORTRAIT OF ADDICTION."

00:05:03.130 --> 00:05:05.700
Man:
I REMEMBER IT ALMOST
AS IF IT WAS TODAY.

00:05:05.700 --> 00:05:08.700
A FRIEND OF MINE
WHO HAD ALREADY BEEN USING

00:05:08.700 --> 00:05:12.530
TOOK ME UP TO THE ROOF,
AND I THOUGHT IT WAS FOR POT--

00:05:12.530 --> 00:05:14.600
UH, MARIJUANA--
AND WE WENT UP THERE

00:05:14.600 --> 00:05:16.870
AND HE HAD ALREADY USED HEROIN.

00:05:16.870 --> 00:05:19.230
HE WAS USING IT INTRAMUSCULAR

00:05:19.230 --> 00:05:22.800
AND SKIN-POPPED IT
AND THEN OFFERED ME SOME.

00:05:22.800 --> 00:05:24.530
AND THERE WAS THIS...

00:05:24.530 --> 00:05:28.770
AS SOON AS I INJECTED IT--
OR HE INJECTED IT FOR ME;

00:05:28.770 --> 00:05:32.230
IN THOSE EARLY DAYS
I HAD A NEEDLE PHOBIA--

00:05:32.230 --> 00:05:35.300
I REMEMBER THIS WARMTH,
THIS SERENITY.

00:05:35.300 --> 00:05:39.130
MY FATHER DEALT WITH
THE FAMILY BY DRINKING.

00:05:39.130 --> 00:05:42.600
HE... I REMEMBER VERY WELL,
HE'D GET A BIG BOTTLE OF ALMADEN

00:05:42.600 --> 00:05:46.130
AND KICK BACK IN FRONT OF THE TV
AND DRINK... DRINK HIS WINE.

00:05:46.130 --> 00:05:47.770
AND AROUND THE TIME I WAS 19

00:05:47.770 --> 00:05:49.670
I TOOK A SEMESTER OFF
FROM SCHOOL

00:05:49.670 --> 00:05:52.500
AND I WAS WORKING
AND COMING HOME WITH THE FAMILY

00:05:52.500 --> 00:05:54.070
AND I DISCOVERED ALCOHOL

00:05:54.070 --> 00:05:57.470
WAS A VERY, VERY EFFICIENT WAY
OF DEALING WITH THE FAMILY.

00:05:57.470 --> 00:06:01.170
AND IT WORKED FOR A WHILE, IT...
YOU KNOW, JUST GET A BUZZ ON

00:06:01.170 --> 00:06:03.630
AND EVERYTHING'S FINE,
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

00:06:03.630 --> 00:06:05.830
IT WAS ON MY FIRST DATE.

00:06:05.830 --> 00:06:09.330
I WENT OUT TO A PLACE CALLED
THE AUDUBON BALLROOM.

00:06:09.330 --> 00:06:12.130
THERE WAS A BIG DANCE THERE

00:06:12.130 --> 00:06:18.170
AND I REMEMBER IT WAS A BOTTLE
OF SEAGRAM'S 7 OR SOMETHING.

00:06:18.170 --> 00:06:21.230
SO, UM, I GOT VERY SICK.

00:06:21.230 --> 00:06:25.700
AND EVEN THAT NIGHT,
MY FIRST TIME DRINKING

00:06:25.700 --> 00:06:29.430
I WAS ABLE TO HOLD
A LOT OF ALCOHOL.

00:06:29.430 --> 00:06:32.100
YOU KNOW, I DIDN'T DRINK
IN HIGH SCHOOL, COLLEGE.

00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:34.630
I HAD NO UPROARIOUS
STORIES THERE.

00:06:34.630 --> 00:06:37.530
I GOT... I STARTED
AFTER I GOT MARRIED

00:06:37.530 --> 00:06:41.870
AND I MOVED TO ANOTHER COMMUNITY
AND I DIDN'T KNOW PEOPLE

00:06:41.870 --> 00:06:45.270
AND WHEN I WENT OUT SOCIALLY,
I WAS VERY SHY.

00:06:45.270 --> 00:06:49.170
BUT I LEARNED IF I HAD A FEW
DRINKS, IT WOULD LOOSEN ME UP.

00:06:49.170 --> 00:06:53.630
I FELT... I FELT AS GOOD
AS EVERYBODY ELSE THERE.

00:06:53.630 --> 00:06:56.800
I CAME HOME FROM TWO YEARS
IN THE ARMED FORCES AND...

00:06:56.800 --> 00:06:58.600
Moyers:
VIETNAM?

00:06:58.600 --> 00:07:00.070
YEAH...

00:07:00.070 --> 00:07:04.000
AND, UM, I HAD AVOIDED
ANY SERIOUS DRUG USE THERE

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:06.770
BUT WHEN I CAME HOME,
I WAS LIVING IN HARLEM.

00:07:06.770 --> 00:07:08.930
ALMOST EVERYONE I KNEW
WAS INVOLVED

00:07:08.930 --> 00:07:11.870
WITH SOME KIND OF DRUGS,
BUT PRINCIPALLY HEROIN

00:07:11.870 --> 00:07:14.870
WHICH WAS SOMETHING
THAT HAD BEEN A TABOO FOR US

00:07:14.870 --> 00:07:16.630
SINCE THE TIME THAT I WAS SMALL.

00:07:16.630 --> 00:07:18.470
WE... WE SORT
OF GREW UP WITH THAT

00:07:18.470 --> 00:07:21.670
BEING A THING THAT WAS FULL OF
MYSTERY, BUT CERTAINLY BAD.

00:07:21.670 --> 00:07:24.700
I'D BEEN VERY TERRIFIED OF
THE NOTION OF ANY KIND OF DRUG.

00:07:24.700 --> 00:07:27.570
I KIND OF THOUGHT I MIGHT HAVE
TO DO THEM AT SOME POINT

00:07:27.570 --> 00:07:29.900
BECAUSE I REMEMBER
DRUG EDUCATION TELLING ME

00:07:29.900 --> 00:07:32.830
THAT PEER PRESSURE IS GOING
TO PUSH YOU INTO DOING DRUGS

00:07:32.830 --> 00:07:34.570
AND I KNEW THAT IF THIS WAS SO

00:07:34.570 --> 00:07:37.370
THEN ANYBODY WHO DOESN'T DO
DRUGS MUST BE A TOTAL GEEK

00:07:37.370 --> 00:07:38.770
AND SINCE I'M A TOTAL GEEK

00:07:38.770 --> 00:07:41.000
AND I WANT TO GET OUT
OF BEING A TOTAL GEEK

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:43.000
I'D BETTER DO
WHAT PEER PRESSURE SAYS.

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:45.830
SO THAT DRUG EDUCATION
WAS NOT PARTICULARLY EFFECTIVE.

00:07:45.830 --> 00:07:48.330
BUT I DO REMEMBER
ONE SORT OF PRINCIPLE

00:07:48.330 --> 00:07:50.930
THAT CAME OUT
OF THAT DRUG EDUCATION WAS

00:07:50.930 --> 00:07:54.830
I REMEMBER THEY TAUGHT ME ABOUT
TOBACCO, AND IT CAUSED CANCER

00:07:54.830 --> 00:07:57.200
AND IT WAS REALLY,
REALLY BAD FOR YOU

00:07:57.200 --> 00:08:00.100
AND IT DIDN'T EVEN SEEM
TO GET YOU PARTICULARLY HIGH

00:08:00.100 --> 00:08:02.330
AND I THOUGHT,
"NAH, I WON'T DO THAT ONE."

00:08:02.330 --> 00:08:05.630
BUT I REMEMBER "ALCOHOL MAKES
YOU PHYSICALLY OUT OF CONTROL.

00:08:05.630 --> 00:08:06.930
"I DON'T LIKE THAT ONE.

00:08:06.930 --> 00:08:09.000
MARIJUANA--
THAT SOUNDS INTERESTING."

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:13.470
I STARTED USING AS A RESULT
OF WORKING UNDERCOVER NARCOTICS

00:08:13.470 --> 00:08:15.470
ON THE STREET LEVEL.

00:08:15.470 --> 00:08:17.970
I WOULD GO INTO A TOWN
WITH AN ASSUMED IDENTITY

00:08:17.970 --> 00:08:19.670
RENT AN APARTMENT AND BUY DRUGS

00:08:19.670 --> 00:08:21.530
FOR A PERIOD OF 60 DAYS
OR 90 DAYS.

00:08:21.530 --> 00:08:23.830
IT SOMETIMES STRETCHED
INTO SEVERAL MONTHS.

00:08:23.830 --> 00:08:26.500
Moyers:
DO YOU REMEMBER
THE FIRST TIME YOU USED?

00:08:26.500 --> 00:08:28.800
I WAS... I HAD A NEIGHBOR
WHO WAS SELLING

00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:30.270
AND I HAD DISCOVERED THIS

00:08:30.270 --> 00:08:32.830
OVER THE COURSE
OF BECOMING FRIENDLY WITH HIM

00:08:32.830 --> 00:08:34.630
AND WENT IN WITH A STATE AGENT.

00:08:34.630 --> 00:08:37.670
HE SAID, "JUST DO LIKE I DO,
DO... DO EXACTLY AS I DO."

00:08:37.670 --> 00:08:40.070
AND THE COCAINE WAS LAID OUT
ON THE MIRROR

00:08:40.070 --> 00:08:41.530
AND... AND HE SNORTED IT

00:08:41.530 --> 00:08:44.430
AND HANDED ME, I THINK IT WAS
A ROLLED-UP $100 BILL

00:08:44.430 --> 00:08:47.700
AND I SNORTED IT, AND I LIKED IT
THE FIRST TIME I DID IT.

00:08:47.700 --> 00:08:50.330
WE WERE ALL OUT IN SUBURBIA,
IN VERY FINE HOMES

00:08:50.330 --> 00:08:52.970
AND HAVING VERY GOOD DINNERS
AND VERY GOOD WINE

00:08:52.970 --> 00:08:56.130
AND THEN IT WAS KIND OF CHIC
TO BRING OUT THE COKE AFTER

00:08:56.130 --> 00:08:58.900
AND THEY'D PUT IT ON A MIRROR
OR A PIECE OF GLASS

00:08:58.900 --> 00:09:01.130
AND BREAK IT UP
AND BREAK UP THE LINES.

00:09:01.130 --> 00:09:03.730
AND WE'D BE TALKING
ABOUT ONE THING OR ANOTHER--

00:09:03.730 --> 00:09:05.330
NEVER ABOUT DRUGS, OF COURSE

00:09:05.330 --> 00:09:08.200
ALWAYS MAYBE ABOUT POLITICS
OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT--

00:09:08.200 --> 00:09:10.200
AND IN THE MIDST
OF OUR CONVERSATION

00:09:10.200 --> 00:09:11.530
WE WOULD BE DOING THIS.

00:09:11.530 --> 00:09:13.970
AND EVERYBODY FELT VERY IN
AND VERY WITH IT

00:09:13.970 --> 00:09:15.630
AND VERY, YOU KNOW, TOGETHER.

00:09:15.630 --> 00:09:17.370
I STARTED CUTTING CLASSES--

00:09:17.370 --> 00:09:19.630
WHICH WAS SOMETHING
THAT I NEVER DID

00:09:19.630 --> 00:09:21.600
BECAUSE I ENJOYED MY CLASSES--

00:09:21.600 --> 00:09:24.870
AND HANGING OUT
IN THE BATHROOMS

00:09:24.870 --> 00:09:28.930
AND DRINKING
WILD IRISH ROSE, YOU KNOW.

00:09:28.930 --> 00:09:34.730
AND AT FIRST,
IT WAS ON A RARE BASIS

00:09:34.730 --> 00:09:37.670
AND THEN IT BECAME
ALMOST A DAILY THING

00:09:37.670 --> 00:09:40.230
THAT YOU START
LOOKING FORWARD TO.

00:09:40.230 --> 00:09:43.200
I HAD TRIED COCAINE FOR THE
FIRST TIME, WHEN I WAS ABOUT 17

00:09:43.200 --> 00:09:44.600
AND I REALLY LIKED

00:09:44.600 --> 00:09:47.600
THE FEELING OF POWER AND GLAMOUR
AND SEXINESS IT GAVE ME.

00:09:47.600 --> 00:09:49.030
AND MY BOYFRIEND SUGGESTED

00:09:49.030 --> 00:09:51.630
"WELL, GEE, YOU'RE GOING
TO THIS IVY LEAGUE SCHOOL

00:09:51.630 --> 00:09:53.100
"THAT'LL BE A GREAT MARKET.

00:09:53.100 --> 00:09:55.930
THERE'S LOTS OF PEOPLE
WITH LOTS OF MONEY THERE."

00:09:55.930 --> 00:09:58.530
AND WHEN I GOT THERE,
I WAS SO INTIMIDATED

00:09:58.530 --> 00:10:01.070
BY ALL THOSE PEOPLE
WITH ALL THAT MONEY.

00:10:01.070 --> 00:10:06.200
I FELT SO LEFT OUT AND
SO SCARED OF THEM AND SO POOR.

00:10:06.200 --> 00:10:07.770
I JUST FELT LIKE, "WELL, GEE

00:10:07.770 --> 00:10:10.130
"HERE'S THIS GREAT SOURCE
OF LOTS OF MONEY.

00:10:10.130 --> 00:10:12.500
"IT'LL GIVE ME FRIENDS,
IT'LL GIVE ME DRUGS

00:10:12.500 --> 00:10:15.370
IT'LL IMPROVE MY SOCIAL LIFE,
PEOPLE WILL WANT ME."

00:10:15.370 --> 00:10:16.800
FRIENDS THAT I GREW UP WITH

00:10:16.800 --> 00:10:19.330
PEOPLE THAT I WAS YOUNG WITH
WERE ALL USING DRUGS

00:10:19.330 --> 00:10:21.170
AND I EITHER FOUND IT OUT
RIGHT AWAY

00:10:21.170 --> 00:10:22.630
OR OVER TIME IT BECAME CLEAR.

00:10:22.630 --> 00:10:25.330
THEY WERE USING HEROIN,
AND, IN FACT, THE...

00:10:25.330 --> 00:10:28.830
IN SOCIAL SITUATIONS-- WE WERE
VERY SOCIAL IN THE '60s--

00:10:28.830 --> 00:10:30.300
AND IN SOCIAL SITUATIONS

00:10:30.300 --> 00:10:33.500
IT SEEMS LIKE THEY HAD A KIND
OF CONNECTION AND CAMARADERIE

00:10:33.500 --> 00:10:35.000
THAT I COULDN'T BREAK INTO.

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:37.430
ACTUALLY, THEY WERE
ON ANOTHER PLANET AND I...

00:10:37.430 --> 00:10:41.030
SPEAKING ANOTHER LANGUAGE, AND I
REALLY COULDN'T BREAK INTO THAT.

00:10:41.030 --> 00:10:43.000
I WAS SOMEWHAT ALIENATED,
AND I...

00:10:43.000 --> 00:10:44.730
I THRASHED AROUND FOR A WHILE

00:10:44.730 --> 00:10:48.200
BUT EVENTUALLY IT WAS OFFERED
TO ME AND I TRIED IT, AND...

00:10:48.200 --> 00:10:50.600
AND WE WERE SNORTING THEN,
AND THEN I WAS...

00:10:50.600 --> 00:10:51.930
I WENT FOR THE IDEA

00:10:51.930 --> 00:10:54.530
THAT IF YOU INHALE IT
RATHER THAN INJECT IT

00:10:54.530 --> 00:10:56.800
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO GET HOOKED ON IT.

00:10:56.800 --> 00:10:58.530
I WANTED TO BELIEVE THAT.

00:10:58.530 --> 00:11:00.870
I STARTED USING WHEN I WAS 19.

00:11:00.870 --> 00:11:04.470
I MAINLINED, UH... COCAINE...
UH, SPEED ACTUALLY

00:11:04.470 --> 00:11:05.900
THEN IT WAS COCAINE

00:11:05.900 --> 00:11:09.630
THEN IT DIDN'T EVEN MATTER,
YOU KNOW, THEN HEROIN.

00:11:09.630 --> 00:11:12.930
AND I FOUND A WAY
OF GETTING OUTSIDE MYSELF.

00:11:17.170 --> 00:11:20.270
Woman:
I WOULD WAKE UP IN THE MORNING

00:11:20.270 --> 00:11:23.100
AND ROLL OVER AND OPEN
MY TOP DRESSER DRAWER

00:11:23.100 --> 00:11:25.070
AND GET THE COCAINE MIRROR OUT

00:11:25.070 --> 00:11:27.530
AND SNORT SOME COCAINE
TO GET STARTED.

00:11:27.530 --> 00:11:30.730
AND THROUGHOUT
THE COURSE OF A DAY...

00:11:30.730 --> 00:11:34.730
TAKE ANOTHER HIT
WHENEVER I FELT I NEEDED IT--

00:11:34.730 --> 00:11:39.400
WHENEVER I WAS...
COMING DOWN TOO FAR.

00:11:39.400 --> 00:11:42.670
