IN ORDER TO MAINTAIN MY HABIT.

00:22:32.530 --> 00:22:34.800
AND THAT DIDN'T...

00:22:34.800 --> 00:22:36.930
I WASN'T SUCCESSFUL FOR LONG

00:22:36.930 --> 00:22:41.530
BECAUSE THE DRUG CULTURE, UNLIKE
THE LARGER SOCIETY'S CULTURE

00:22:41.530 --> 00:22:44.700
IS A CULTURE WHERE
YOU START OFF AT THE TOP

00:22:44.700 --> 00:22:46.330
AND YOU QUICKLY GO
TO THE BOTTOM

00:22:46.330 --> 00:22:48.630
WHERE, IN SOCIETY,
YOU START OFF AT THE BOTTOM

00:22:48.630 --> 00:22:50.030
AND YOU WORK YOUR WAY UP.

00:22:50.030 --> 00:22:52.970
SO I WORKED MY WAY DOWN QUICKLY,
IN LESS THAN A YEAR.

00:22:52.970 --> 00:22:57.530
EVERYBODY AROUND ME DRANK,
AND NOBODY ELSE WAS WORKING.

00:22:57.530 --> 00:23:00.770
IT WAS THE LIFESTYLE FOR ME.

00:23:00.770 --> 00:23:03.930
BUT I GUESS WHEN I STARTED
HAVING BLACKOUTS

00:23:03.930 --> 00:23:07.770
WHEN I STARTED HAVING
THOSE EXPERIENCES

00:23:07.770 --> 00:23:13.430
WHERE I COULDN'T REMEMBER
HOW I GOT HOME OR WHERE I WAS

00:23:13.430 --> 00:23:16.100
OR THINGS LIKE THAT

00:23:16.100 --> 00:23:19.830
SOMETHING STARTED GOING OFF
IN ME THAT SOMETHING IS WRONG.

00:23:19.830 --> 00:23:21.170
I GOT PRETTY DRUNK

00:23:21.170 --> 00:23:23.270
AND RAN OUT IN THE RAIN
IN MY UNDERWEAR--

00:23:23.270 --> 00:23:24.730
UNDERWEAR HAPPENED TO BE RED;

00:23:24.730 --> 00:23:26.700
THAT FIGURES
INTO THE STORY LATER--

00:23:26.700 --> 00:23:28.930
AND WAS JUST SHOUTING,
HOOTING AND HOLLERING

00:23:28.930 --> 00:23:30.570
NOTHING BIG,
NOT THAT BIG A DEAL

00:23:30.570 --> 00:23:31.930
BUT MY DOWNSTAIRS NEIGHBOR

00:23:31.930 --> 00:23:33.600
DIDN'T PARTICULARLY
APPRECIATE IT

00:23:33.600 --> 00:23:36.070
AND SHE CALLED THE COPS,
AND THE COPS SHOWED UP

00:23:36.070 --> 00:23:40.070
AND I HAD TO SHOW UP
IN COURT THE FOLLOWING WEEK.

00:23:40.070 --> 00:23:42.800
AND THE JUDGE IS READING
THE LITTLE DOCUMENT

00:23:42.800 --> 00:23:45.230
AND SAYS, "YOU WERE OUTSIDE
IN THE RAIN

00:23:45.230 --> 00:23:46.870
IN YOUR...<i> RED</i> UNDERWEAR!"

00:23:46.870 --> 00:23:50.670
HE WAS APPARENTLY JUST APPALLED
THAT MY UNDERWEAR WAS RED.

00:23:50.670 --> 00:23:52.970
BUT, YOU KNOW, THAT'S A SIGN.

00:23:52.970 --> 00:23:56.230
IF THE COPS ARE SHOWING UP,
THAT'S PROBABLY A SIGN.

00:23:56.230 --> 00:24:00.630
I THINK THE TIME
IT REALLY HIT HOME WAS

00:24:00.630 --> 00:24:03.300
WHEN I HAD BEGUN INJECTING IT

00:24:03.300 --> 00:24:06.630
AND I FOUND MYSELF
CRAWLING ON THE FLOOR

00:24:06.630 --> 00:24:11.300
SEARCHING THE CARPET FOR
ONE MORE LITTLE ROCK OF COCAINE.

00:24:11.300 --> 00:24:15.300
I MEAN, THIS LED ME
THROUGH SOME BOUTS WITH PRISON.

00:24:15.300 --> 00:24:17.800
I MEAN, I BECAME A THIEF

00:24:17.800 --> 00:24:24.400
IN ORDER TO SUPPORT A HABIT
THAT WAS REALLY EXPENSIVE.

00:24:24.400 --> 00:24:26.070
THERE WAS NO JOB YOU CAN HAVE

00:24:26.070 --> 00:24:28.170
THAT COULD SUPPORT
A SPEEDBALL HABIT.

00:24:28.170 --> 00:24:30.570
I MEAN, YOU EITHER HAVE TO HAVE
OLD WEALTH

00:24:30.570 --> 00:24:34.900
OR YOU HAVE TO TAKE MONEY
WHERE IT LIES.

00:24:34.900 --> 00:24:36.570
AND SO THIS LED ME TO...

00:24:36.570 --> 00:24:38.970
I MEAN, THERE WERE PERIODS
THAT I SPENT ALONE

00:24:38.970 --> 00:24:41.630
WHERE I WAS JUST LIVING
ON THE FRINGES OF SOCIETY

00:24:41.630 --> 00:24:43.130
IF I WAS LIVING AT ALL.

00:24:43.130 --> 00:24:45.730
I LIVED IN A NICE HOUSE,
I HAD A BUNCH OF CARS

00:24:45.730 --> 00:24:49.230
MY KIDS WERE IN PRIVATE SCHOOLS,
YOU KNOW, I LOOKED ALL RIGHT.

00:24:49.230 --> 00:24:52.400
WHAT WAS THE PROBLEM?

00:24:52.400 --> 00:24:54.400
THE PROBLEM WAS I WAS DYING.

00:24:54.400 --> 00:24:56.300
YOU KNOW, I WAS DYING.

00:24:56.300 --> 00:24:59.570
18 YEARS LATER AND A MARRIAGE
AND AN ABANDONMENT

00:24:59.570 --> 00:25:03.470
AND ESTRANGEMENT FROM MY SON
AND A ZILLION OTHER THINGS

00:25:03.470 --> 00:25:05.300
ALSO THREE CAREERS--

00:25:05.300 --> 00:25:08.800
I'D HAD PERIODS
OF INTERMITTENT ABSTINENCE--

00:25:08.800 --> 00:25:12.330
UM... THREE CAREERS

00:25:12.330 --> 00:25:17.670
WHERE I JUST WAS ABOUT TO MOVE
OVER THE HUMP, SO TO SPEAK

00:25:17.670 --> 00:25:20.730
INTO UNKNOWN TERRITORY
OF SUCCESS

00:25:20.730 --> 00:25:22.870
I WOULD ALWAYS FALL
INTO ADDICTION AGAIN.

00:25:22.870 --> 00:25:24.900
THEN THERE WAS A POINT--

00:25:24.900 --> 00:25:27.770
AND I CAN'T REMEMBER EXACTLY
WHEN IT HAPPENED

00:25:27.770 --> 00:25:29.900
I JUST REMEMBER
THAT IT HAPPENED--

00:25:29.900 --> 00:25:34.070
THERE WAS A POINT
WHEN I WOULD DO IT EVERY DAY.

00:25:34.070 --> 00:25:38.100
I WOULD HAVE IT AND I WOULD
COMPULSIVELY DO IT EVERY DAY

00:25:38.100 --> 00:25:41.600
EVEN THOUGH
I DIDN'T REALLY ENJOY IT

00:25:41.600 --> 00:25:43.270
WHICH SOUNDS VERY STRANGE

00:25:43.270 --> 00:25:45.930
BUT NEVERTHELESS,
THAT'S THE WAY IT WAS.

00:25:45.930 --> 00:25:48.700
I USED COCAINE
FOR ABOUT TEN YEARS

00:25:48.700 --> 00:25:51.600
NEVER MISSED A WEEKEND
IN TEN YEARS

00:25:51.600 --> 00:25:55.770
NEVER MISSED FRIDAY,
SATURDAY AND SUNDAY.

00:25:55.770 --> 00:26:00.170
BINGES OF COCAINE USE
FOR TEN YEARS.

00:26:00.170 --> 00:26:02.500
WHAT WERE YOU LIKE
IN THOSE BINGES?

00:26:02.500 --> 00:26:03.670
VIOLENT.

00:26:03.670 --> 00:26:05.330
I MEAN, YOU BEGIN...

00:26:05.330 --> 00:26:07.200
THIS BEGINS OVER TIME.

00:26:07.200 --> 00:26:11.000
YOU BEGIN GREGARIOUS,
INTERESTING, VERY SOCIAL

00:26:11.000 --> 00:26:13.330
AND YOU END UP...

00:26:13.330 --> 00:26:19.270
YOU END UP PARANOID,
ANGRY, UH...

00:26:20.430 --> 00:26:24.200
ASSAULTIVE, OUT OF CONTROL.

00:26:24.200 --> 00:26:26.470
IT'S FUNNY BECAUSE THE MOMENT
I GOT ARRESTED

00:26:26.470 --> 00:26:29.130
FOR A VERY BRIEF MOMENT,
I FELT THIS SENSE OF RELIEF

00:26:29.130 --> 00:26:30.630
BECAUSE I WAS LIKE

00:26:30.630 --> 00:26:33.600
"OH, THE WORST THAT COULD HAPPEN
HAS HAPPENED, IT'S OVER."

00:26:33.600 --> 00:26:38.400
AND, YOU KNOW, THEN, YOU KNOW,
BEING IN JAIL WAS TERRIFYING

00:26:38.400 --> 00:26:41.470
BUT I HAVE TO SAY,
THE MOMENT I GOT OUT

00:26:41.470 --> 00:26:44.570
I WENT BACK TO MY APARTMENT
AND I FOUND SOME DRUGS

00:26:44.570 --> 00:26:46.600
THAT I KNEW THE COPS
HADN'T FOUND

00:26:46.600 --> 00:26:50.430
AND I KNEW WHERE THEY WERE,
AND I WENT AND I GOT THEM

00:26:50.430 --> 00:26:53.600
AND I INJECTED THEM AND...

00:26:53.600 --> 00:26:57.100
I MEAN, NOW,
HOW IRRATIONAL CAN YOU GET?

00:26:57.100 --> 00:26:59.100
YOU'VE JUST BEEN ARRESTED
FOR THIS STUFF

00:26:59.100 --> 00:27:01.700
AND THEN WHAT DO YOU DO,
BUT AS SOON AS YOU GO HOME

00:27:01.700 --> 00:27:03.030
YOU DO THIS?

00:27:03.030 --> 00:27:07.000
I DIDN'T GO DANCE
ON TOP OF A BAR SOMEWHERE.

00:27:07.000 --> 00:27:09.430
YOU KNOW, I DIDN'T GRAB
OTHER PEOPLE'S HUSBANDS.

00:27:09.430 --> 00:27:10.830
I DIDN'T DO ANY OF THAT

00:27:10.830 --> 00:27:13.070
WHICH SUPPOSEDLY I THOUGHT
WERE THE "HALLMARKS."

00:27:13.070 --> 00:27:14.700
YOU KNOW, THIS IS WHAT YOU DID.

00:27:14.700 --> 00:27:16.070
I DIDN'T DO ANY OF THAT.

00:27:16.070 --> 00:27:19.930
I WAS SO BORING, JUST DAY
AFTER DAY OF FEELING...

00:27:19.930 --> 00:27:22.030
LIKE A PIECE OF JUNK.

00:27:22.030 --> 00:27:23.600
IT'S A HELL.

00:27:23.600 --> 00:27:25.370
IT'S REALLY...

00:27:25.370 --> 00:27:30.270
YOUR LIFE BECOMES ABOUT WHERE
AM I GOING TO GET THE NEXT DOSE?

00:27:30.270 --> 00:27:33.270
YOU'RE DISCONNECTED
FROM FRIENDS AND FAMILY.

00:27:33.270 --> 00:27:36.000
YOUR EMOTIONS ARE DULLED

00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:39.970
TO THE POINT OF
ALMOST BEING NONEXISTENT.

00:27:39.970 --> 00:27:42.670
THERE'S NO LIFE,
THERE'S NO LIFE.

00:27:42.670 --> 00:27:46.570
THERE'S NO SOUL,
THERE'S NO SPIRIT LEFT IN YOU.

00:27:46.570 --> 00:27:51.300
I COULDN'T IMAGINE A LIFE
THAT I WOULD BE HAPPY IN.

00:27:52.970 --> 00:27:56.630
I COULDN'T IMAGINE LIFE
WORKING OUT IN ANY KIND OF WAY

00:27:56.630 --> 00:28:00.370
TO ACCOMMODATE ME.

00:28:00.370 --> 00:28:02.030
UM...

00:28:04.200 --> 00:28:06.200
YOU KNOW, WHAT I WOULD
LIKE TO DO...

00:28:06.200 --> 00:28:09.530
WOULD HAVE LIKED TO DO IF
I COULD IS GET A PLACE TO LIVE

00:28:09.530 --> 00:28:11.700
AND GET AN UNLIMITED SUPPLY
OF ALCOHOL

00:28:11.700 --> 00:28:13.500
AND JUST CONTINUE
TO DRINK AND DRINK.

00:28:13.500 --> 00:28:16.270
THAT WOULD HAVE BEEN FINE
IF THAT HAD BEEN OFFERED TO ME

00:28:16.270 --> 00:28:17.930
IF SOME ECCENTRIC
MILLIONAIRE SAID

00:28:17.930 --> 00:28:20.030
"ALL RIGHT, IF YOU'D LIKE,
I'LL PROVIDE YOU

00:28:20.030 --> 00:28:22.870
"WITH AN APARTMENT AND ENOUGH
FOOD TO KEEP YOURSELF ALIVE

00:28:22.870 --> 00:28:24.370
AND ALL THE ALCOHOL YOU WANT."

00:28:24.370 --> 00:28:26.130
"THANK YOU," YOU KNOW,
"THAT'S FINE.

00:28:26.130 --> 00:28:27.800
THAT'S FINE, I'LL JUST DO THAT."

00:28:27.800 --> 00:28:32.170
I WAS IN
A RELATIONSHIP THEN, UH...

00:28:32.170 --> 00:28:35.470
WITH A LOVELY WOMAN
WHO I PUT THROUGH MUCH SUFFERING

00:28:35.470 --> 00:28:38.630
BECAUSE OF MY ESCALATING
ADDICTION OVER THE YEARS

00:28:38.630 --> 00:28:40.130
AND BINGEING

00:28:40.130 --> 00:28:41.530
AND SHE WAS BECOMING

00:28:41.530 --> 00:28:44.330
BOTH PSYCHOLOGICALLY
AND PHYSICALLY SICK

00:28:44.330 --> 00:28:46.570
AND, UH, SHE LEFT ME.

00:28:46.570 --> 00:28:51.430
SHE WAS SMART ENOUGH
AND WISE ENOUGH TO LEAVE ME

00:28:51.430 --> 00:28:56.230
AND, UH, A WOMAN WHO I CARED FOR
AND LOVED VERY MUCH

00:28:56.230 --> 00:29:00.270
AND YET SHE PLAYED A...
SHE PLAYED AN IMPORTANT ROLE.

00:29:00.270 --> 00:29:01.600
SHE...

00:29:01.600 --> 00:29:04.970
SHE... SHE WOULD...

00:29:07.830 --> 00:29:11.370
KEEP ME IN SOME WAYS

00:29:11.370 --> 00:29:12.900
ONLY... ONLY ADDICTED

00:29:12.900 --> 00:29:16.030
THOSE THURSDAYS, FRIDAYS,
SATURDAYS AND SUNDAYS.

00:29:16.030 --> 00:29:17.470
I WOULDN'T GO BEYOND THAT

00:29:17.470 --> 00:29:19.730
BECAUSE SHE WOULD
COMPLAIN AND HARASS ME

00:29:19.730 --> 00:29:22.330
AND SO THAT WAS
THE EXTERNAL CONTROL

00:29:22.330 --> 00:29:24.830
THAT KEPT ME
FROM USING EVEN MORE.

00:29:24.830 --> 00:29:27.570
SHE FINALLY ENDED UP LEAVING.

00:29:27.570 --> 00:29:34.270
UH, AND EVEN WHEN I LOVED HER
VERY PASSIONATELY

00:29:34.270 --> 00:29:36.670
AND WOULD MISS HER

00:29:36.670 --> 00:29:39.700
I REMEMBER MY FIRST THOUGHT WAS,
"WHEW, GLAD SHE'S GONE.

00:29:39.700 --> 00:29:42.100
"YOU KNOW, NOW I CAN
REALLY STRETCH OUT HERE

00:29:42.100 --> 00:29:43.530
AND ENJOY MYSELF."

00:29:47.530 --> 00:29:50.070
IT WAS VERY FRIGHTENING
TO DISCOVER

00:29:50.070 --> 00:29:52.230
THAT I ACTUALLY HAD
AN ADDICTION

00:29:52.230 --> 00:29:54.870
AND STARTED
IMMEDIATELY TRYING TO, UH...

00:29:54.870 --> 00:29:57.570
TO WITHDRAW FROM IT
AND GET AWAY FROM IT.

00:29:57.570 --> 00:29:58.800
WHAT DID
YOU DO?

00:29:58.800 --> 00:30:01.070
I TRIED...
WELL, A COUPLE OF TIMES

00:30:01.070 --> 00:30:04.670
I TRIED JUST COLD WITHDRAWAL
WITH SOMEBODY HELPING ME

00:30:04.670 --> 00:30:08.830
AND I FOUND BEFORE TOO LONG I
WAS ENTIRELY TOO WEAK FOR THAT.

00:30:08.830 --> 00:30:10.130
I JUST DIDN'T HAVE

00:30:10.130 --> 00:30:12.630
THE STAMINA AND
THE MORAL CONVICTION FOR THAT.

00:30:12.630 --> 00:30:15.370
EVERY SINGLE DAY I WOULD WAKE UP

00:30:15.370 --> 00:30:18.430
AND I'D SAY,
"TODAY'S THE DAY I STOP"

00:30:18.430 --> 00:30:21.470
AND BY 3:00 OR 4:00
EVERY SINGLE DAY

00:30:21.470 --> 00:30:23.100
I KNEW THAT I WOULD, UH...

00:30:23.100 --> 00:30:25.670
I KNEW THAT I'D HAVE
TO DRINK THAT NIGHT.

00:30:25.670 --> 00:30:28.730
AND THEN I'D SAY, "WELL,
I'M GOING TO STOP AT TWO

00:30:28.730 --> 00:30:29.830
OR STOP AT THREE."

00:30:29.830 --> 00:30:31.930
AND I WENT TO MASS EVERY MORNING

00:30:31.930 --> 00:30:34.930
AND I WOULD PRAY THAT
I COULD STOP AT THREE DRINKS

00:30:34.930 --> 00:30:37.670
WHICH IN FACT I DID,
BUT THEY WERE IN VATS.

00:30:37.670 --> 00:30:39.200
(<i> Moyers laughs</i> )

00:30:39.200 --> 00:30:42.930
I MEAN, MY SITUATION WAS UNUSUAL
IN THAT I WAS A POLICE OFFICER.

00:30:42.930 --> 00:30:44.430
I WASN'T, UM, SOMEONE

00:30:44.430 --> 00:30:47.030
WHO WAS JUST STRUGGLING
AGAINST AN ADDICTION.

00:30:47.030 --> 00:30:49.230
I WAS IN THIS... THIS WORLD

00:30:49.230 --> 00:30:52.030
WHERE I WOULD LOSE
MY JOB IMMEDIATELY

00:30:52.030 --> 00:30:56.230
AND MIGHT GO TO PRISON IF
I ADMITTED WHAT I WAS DOING.

00:30:56.230 --> 00:30:59.300
BUT AT A CERTAIN POINT,
I REALIZED...

00:30:59.300 --> 00:31:01.330
IN THE LAST INVESTIGATION
I WAS DOING

00:31:01.330 --> 00:31:03.100
THAT... THAT I WAS STRUNG OUT

00:31:03.100 --> 00:31:06.000
AND I FEARED THAT MY PARTNER
WAS KILLING HIMSELF.

00:31:06.000 --> 00:31:07.070
USING?

00:31:07.070 --> 00:31:08.130
YES.

00:31:08.130 --> 00:31:09.830
YOU KNEW HE WAS
ADDICTED, TOO?

00:31:09.830 --> 00:31:11.000
OH, ABSOLUTELY.

00:31:11.000 --> 00:31:12.330
AND YOU
WERE ADDICTED?

00:31:12.330 --> 00:31:14.400
YES, AND I WENT TO THE SERGEANT

00:31:14.400 --> 00:31:16.700
AND SAID,
"WE'VE GOT DRUG PROBLEMS"

00:31:16.700 --> 00:31:19.800
AND THEY PUT HIM IN THE HOSPITAL
FOR A FEW DAYS

00:31:19.800 --> 00:31:23.400
AND HE GOT BACK OUT AND
THEY SAID, "GO BUY MORE DRUGS."

00:31:23.400 --> 00:31:25.630
THEY WANTED CASES,
THEY WANTED NUMBERS.

00:31:25.630 --> 00:31:27.130
THEY DIDN'T CARE

00:31:27.130 --> 00:31:30.330
THAT THEIR NARCOTICS OPERATIVES
WERE STRUNG OUT ON DRUGS.

00:31:30.330 --> 00:31:31.370
IT DIDN'T MATTER.

00:31:31.370 --> 00:31:34.300
I WAS IN A BATTLE FOR MY LIFE

00:31:34.300 --> 00:31:37.530
WITH THIS THING
CALLED ALCOHOLISM.

00:31:37.530 --> 00:31:40.600
AND...

00:31:40.600 --> 00:31:44.630
MY ALCOHOL TOLD ME,
"CUT YOUR FACE."

00:31:44.630 --> 00:31:48.330
I WENT TO A MIRROR,
I WAS LIVING IN BROOKLYN

00:31:48.330 --> 00:31:52.070
AND I TOOK A RAZOR BLADE
AND I CUT ONE SIDE OF MY FACE.

00:31:52.070 --> 00:31:54.300
I CUT THIS SIDE,
AND I STOOD THERE

00:31:54.300 --> 00:31:56.200
AND I REMEMBER THIS VIVIDLY.

00:31:56.200 --> 00:31:58.170
I WASN'T IN A BLACKOUT.

00:31:58.170 --> 00:32:02.030
UM, AND THEN IT TOLD ME,
"CUT THE OTHER SIDE"

00:32:02.030 --> 00:32:03.670
SO I DID THAT AS WELL.

00:32:03.670 --> 00:32:06.270
I HAD A GUN IN MY POCKET

00:32:06.270 --> 00:32:09.130
AND OBVIOUSLY I WAS LOOKING
FOR SOMEONE WHO HAD DRUGS

00:32:09.130 --> 00:32:12.070
AND THERE'S NO ONE OUT
AT THAT KIND OF... KIND OF TIME

00:32:12.070 --> 00:32:15.030
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE MORNING,
IN THE SOUTH BRONX AGAIN

00:32:15.030 --> 00:32:18.970
AND, UH... AND I'M 25.

00:32:18.970 --> 00:32:22.000
AND JUST REALIZING,
"I'M GOING TO BE LIKE THIS

00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:23.700
"FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE--

00:32:23.700 --> 00:32:26.000
THIS IS WHAT I'M
GOING TO BE LIKE."

00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:30.570
I'M TALKING ABOUT 1968,
PROBABLY... '67, '68

00:32:30.570 --> 00:32:37.270
WHERE THE AXIOM, CLICHE, "ONCE
AN ADDICT, ALWAYS AN ADDICT"

00:32:37.270 --> 00:32:39.800
WAS VERY MUCH AN ACCEPTED ONE.

00:32:39.800 --> 00:32:44.870
AND THAT'S FRIGHTENING TO THINK
I'M ONLY GOING TO GET WORSE.

00:32:44.870 --> 00:32:48.230
I'M GOING TO LOSE ALL MY TEETH,
I'M GOING TO LOSE AN EYE.

00:32:48.230 --> 00:32:51.100
I'M GOING TO SUFFER
AND I'M GOING TO BE MISERABLE

00:32:51.100 --> 00:32:54.900
WALKING AROUND THE STREETS LIKE
THIS IN THE MIDDLE OF FEBRUARY

00:32:54.900 --> 00:32:58.230
ZERO DEGREES, WALKING AROUND
LOOKING FOR SOMEONE TO ROB.

00:32:58.230 --> 00:33:02.570
I THINK... THE THOUGHTS WERE,
"I SHOULD KILL MYSELF.

00:33:02.570 --> 00:33:07.030
WHY WOULD I WANT TO LIVE
LIKE THIS 20, 30 MORE YEARS?"

00:33:07.030 --> 00:33:08.500
I KEPT BUYING DRUGS.

00:33:08.500 --> 00:33:11.970
EVENTUALLY, MY PARTNER
AND I WOUND UP GETTING SHOT

00:33:11.970 --> 00:33:13.830
AND I LEFT THE DEPARTMENT.

00:33:13.830 --> 00:33:17.370
GETTING SHOT WAS, UM...

00:33:17.370 --> 00:33:20.930
WAS A FORM OF DEATH

00:33:20.930 --> 00:33:22.370
FOR A LONG TIME.

00:33:22.370 --> 00:33:26.100
AND I RELIED ON PRESCRIPTION
DRUGS VERY HEAVILY

00:33:26.100 --> 00:33:28.230
FOR A LONG TIME AFTER THAT

00:33:28.230 --> 00:33:31.030
INSTEAD OF DEALING
WITH THE TERROR.

00:33:31.030 --> 00:33:32.230
I WANTED TO DIE.

00:33:32.230 --> 00:33:33.900
I REMEMBER THINKING AT POINTS

00:33:33.900 --> 00:33:37.200
"I'M JUST GOING TO RAISE THESE
CHILDREN AND THEN I'LL DIE."

00:33:37.200 --> 00:33:39.500
AND I THINK, REALLY,
INITIALLY I GOT SOBER

00:33:39.500 --> 00:33:42.530
JUST BECAUSE-- I SMOKED
MY HEAD OFF AT THAT POINT--

00:33:42.530 --> 00:33:43.930
I WOULD SMOKE IN BED

00:33:43.930 --> 00:33:46.700
AND I WAS AFRAID THE HOUSE
WAS GOING TO BURN DOWN

00:33:46.700 --> 00:33:48.030
AND I WOULD...

00:33:48.030 --> 00:33:50.500
YOU KNOW, THE KIDS
WOULD BE BURNED TO DEATH.

